-Methods in Java are used to describe the actions
-These are of 2 types - Concrete (Which has a body) Abstract (Which doesn't have a body)
-Methods can Parameterized and Non-Parameterized 
-Method Signature means Method Name and it's parameters
-A method can't be created inside another method
-A method can be only Called inside another method. Like in MAIN() we call many other methods 
- If a method doesn't return anything then the return type would be void
- Method are of two types - Abstract and Concrete(Parameterised and non-Parameterised method)
Abstract Method - The method that does not has method body
Concrete - Which has a body 

- Method can be Overloaded and Overridden.